Per institutional audit: earnings + earnings-analysis + earnings-guidance +
calendars all shared the same universe (portfolio + watchlist) and same data
model. Three of the four scored guidance / margin / capex from the same
endpoints. Forced the user to mentally reconcile four near-identical surfaces.

New /earnings-hub route with internal sub-tabs:
  📅 Calendar    — monthly earnings calendar with quality grade  (was /calendars)
  📈 Scan        — quarterly Revenue/Margin/EPS grid + grade     (was /earnings)
  📊 Guidance    — last-45-day guidance signals                   (was /earnings-guidance)
  🔬 Concall AI  — concall transcript + filing PDF AI report      (was /earnings-analysis)

Implementation: dynamic-imports the four existing pages as components.
Only the active sub-tab mounts so hidden tabs do not run their (often
expensive) queries. URL state via ?tab=calendar|scan|guidance|concall
preserves active sub-tab on refresh / share.

Sidebar: 'Earnings' + 'Earnings AI' + 'Calendar' replaced by single
'Earnings' entry pointing to /earnings-hub. Old routes kept alive for
deeplink compatibility. Sidebar nav 14 -> 12 entries.

Cumulative cleanup across 0089-0091: nav reduced 16 -> 12, 5 duplicate
surfaces collapsed (portfolios, macro-maps, heatmap, movers, calendars,
earnings-analysis), 0 features lost.
